RSCx Mixed Analysis

Lorenz Oehler

2023-10-05

Introduction

This document is about the Immunohistochemistry that was used to deternine the expression of CNPase, which is an enzym which is primarily expressed in oligodendrocytes and is responsible for producing myelin sheaths around axons.

On of the obstacles I had to face was the use of two different Microskops. Thus I decided to use the standardized z-Score for both of the Microskopes for the plots.

I will first startwith a descriptive analysis an plotting the Plot section. Later I will do a statistical analysis.

AFIU explained

AFIU (Arbitrary Flourescence Intensity Unit) is an acronym I used to describe the flourescence Intensity, which is our measurement for the the expresssion of CNPase.

The basis of the Measurement is the CTCF (El-Sharkawey (2016)), but because were not interested in the flourescence Intensity of a singel cell, we devidid the value of the CTCF by the area, which was selected in imagej. The special aspect of the CTCF is, that it takes the background intensity into account.

This is the Formula of the CTCF:

\(IntegratedDenisty - (AreaOfSelectedCell \times MeanFlourescenceReadingOfBackground)\)

The full formula of that we thus used to determine the flourescence Intensity is this:

\(\frac{(IntegratedDenisty - (AreaOfSelectedCell \times MeanFlourescenceReadingOfBackground))}{AreaOfSelectedCell}\)

## Prep
### load data

data_RS_only <- readRDS("../data/clean_data/Retrospinalcortex_AFIU_01.RDS")
data_RS_only_mean <- readRDS("../data/clean_data/Retrospinalcortex_AFIU_mean_01.RDS")

# Define colors
data_RS <- readRDS("../data/clean_data/Retrospinalcortex_only_AFIU_01.RDS")
data_RS_mean <- readRDS("../data/clean_data/Retrospinalcortex_only_AFIU_mean_01.RDS")

## add column for z score (AFIU) for plotting
data_RS_only$mean_AFIU <- mean(data_RS_only$AFIU)
data_RS_only$sd_AFIU <- sd(data_RS_only$AFIU)
data_RS_only$zAFIU <- (data_RS_only$AFIU - data_RS_only$mean_AFIU)/data_RS_only$sd_AFIU

data_RS_only_mean$mean_AFIU <- mean(data_RS_only_mean$AFIU)
data_RS_only_mean$sd_AFIU <- sd(data_RS_only_mean$AFIU)
data_RS_only_mean$zAFIU <- (data_RS_only_mean$AFIU - data_RS_only_mean$mean_AFIU)/data_RS_only_mean$sd_AFIU

data_RS$mean_AFIU <- mean(data_RS$AFIU)
data_RS$sd_AFIU <- sd(data_RS$AFIU)
data_RS$zAFIU <- (data_RS$AFIU - data_RS$mean_AFIU)/data_RS$sd_AFIU

data_RS_mean$mean_AFIU <- mean(data_RS_mean$AFIU)
data_RS_mean$sd_AFIU <- sd(data_RS_mean$AFIU)
data_RS_mean$zAFIU <- (data_RS_mean$AFIU - data_RS_mean$mean_AFIU)/data_RS_mean$sd_AFIU

## ad value for mikroskope
microscope1 <- "microscope1"
microscope2 <- "microscope2"

## add column with microscope name
data_RS_only$microscope <- microscope1
data_RS_only_mean$microscope <- microscope1

data_RS$microscope <- microscope2
data_RS_mean$microscope <- microscope2

### create one single data frame
data <- rbind(data_RS_only,data_RS)
data_mean <- rbind(data_RS_only_mean,data_RS_mean)




Color_RID_mapping <- readRDS("../Preprocessing/Definitions/Color_RID_mapping.RData") 
colors_list <- readRDS("../Preprocessing/Definitions/colors_list.RData")

Plots

Boxplots

Plots by RID by Region

All of the Values in this section have been preprocessed and the values that are seen are the mean of multiple slices (if available).

The Graph shows the zScore of the AFIU for the Subjects (RID) separate for each cortex region (RSD and RSG). Individual where only one hemisphere was available clearly stand out due to their non existent variance.

We can see, that most of the variance within the IDs is fairly small and that increased enrichment of the environment, leads to a higher Intensity.

axis_labels <- c("RSG","RSD")

Region1 <- subset(data_mean,BrainRegion == "RSG")
Region2 <- subset(data_mean,BrainRegion == "RSD")

breaks_vec <- c("CB","CS","EX","EE")

Statistical Analysis

ANOVA

The ANOVA showed significant group differences, but no effect of the hemisphere.

As we can see no difference between the two control groups. Both the Exercise (EX) group and the enriched environment (EE) show significantly higher expression than the control groups (CB, CS). The EE group In the RSD the EE group also shows a significant higher value than the EX group.
